\sum_{j=0}^{k} {a+j \choose j} = {a+k+1 \choose k}.
{a+j \choose j} = \frac{(a+j)!}{j!(a+j-j)!} = \frac{(a+j)!}{j!a!}
\sum_{j=0}^{k} {a+j \choose j} = {a+k \choose k} +\sum_{j=0}^{k-1} {a+j \choose j} = [help!] = {a+k+1 \choose k}
\sum_{j=0}^k\binom{a+j}j=\binom{a+k+1}k\tag{1}
